233
00:13:00,398 --> 00:13:01,115
Light.

234
00:13:01,894 --> 00:13:05,022
There is light when

235
00:13:05,290 --> 00:13:07,172
we start perceiving an object.

236
00:13:07,174 --> 00:13:10,110
When we 'see' an object,

237
00:13:10,135 --> 00:13:12,196
we're not perceiving the object itself.

238
00:13:12,221 --> 00:13:13,810
We're perceiving it because

239
00:13:13,835 --> 00:13:16,897
we see the light bouncing off the object.

240
00:13:17,115 --> 00:13:20,069
So, when we see an object,

241
00:13:20,094 --> 00:13:22,643
light is an essential element.

242
00:13:22,827 --> 00:13:25,953
I just mentioned that objects reflect light.

243
00:13:25,954 --> 00:13:27,618
Let's find out about this.

244
00:13:27,702 --> 00:13:31,063
Basically, an object reflects light differently

245
00:13:31,088 --> 00:13:32,815
