249
00:13:41,773 --> 00:13:43,950
On the other hand, when there's no color,

250
00:13:43,975 --> 00:13:45,208
there would be black light.

251
00:13:46,708 --> 00:13:49,382
So, all the colors are included in sunlight.

252
00:13:49,383 --> 00:13:50,563
What does that mean?

253
00:13:50,588 --> 00:13:52,658
Let's say a rainbow is formed here.

254
00:13:53,783 --> 00:13:54,683
The rainbow is here,

255
00:13:54,708 --> 00:13:58,037
and let's say the character has

256
00:14:01,352 --> 00:14:02,731
a yellow object.

257
00:14:06,277 --> 00:14:07,721
If it's a yellow object,

258
00:14:07,775 --> 00:14:10,699
what kind of light would it reflect?

259
00:14:10,700 --> 00:14:12,292
This object

260
00:14:12,317 --> 00:14:14,727
reflects yellow, just like its original color.

261
00:14:16,402 --> 00:14:19,781
Then, what happens to the other light colors?

262
00:14:19,782 --> 00:14:21,524
The object just absorbs it.

263
00:14:23,098 --> 00:14:25,477
What phenomenon happens because of this?

264
00:14:25,502 --> 00:14:28,021
You know when we have black shirts and white shirts,

265
00:14:28,046 --> 00:14:30,935
